# Pine Script v6 — Cline Rules
# Author: Ugur Pala · mail@ugurpala.com · github.com/trugurpala/pinescriptv6
# TR: Cline, Roo, Continue ve Aider için kural dosyası
# EN: Rules for Cline, Roo, Continue, and Aider

## Protocol

Before writing any Pine Script v6 code:
1. Read LESSONS_LEARNED.md (known errors and fixes)
2. Check LLM_MANIFEST.md (find the correct reference file)
3. Read that reference file
4. Write the code
5. On error: solve + append to LESSONS_LEARNED.md

## Rules

- //@version=6 on every script — no exceptions
- Use ta.* functions — never reimplement manually
- Use input.int(), input.float() etc — NOT bare input()
- Use request.security() — NOT security()
- Use indicator() — NOT study()
- var / varip per execution model
- No invented function names

## Reference Map

| Task | File |
|------|------|
| RSI, EMA, MACD, ATR | reference/functions/ta.md |
| strategy.entry, exit | reference/functions/strategy.md |
| plot, line, label | reference/functions/drawing.md |
| request.security, MTF | reference/functions/request.md |
| array, map | reference/functions/collections.md |
| math, str, input, alert | reference/functions/general.md |
| Errors | concepts/common_errors.md |
| Execution model | concepts/execution_model.md |
| **Always first** | LESSONS_LEARNED.md |

## On Error

```
### [Error title]
- **Error message:** exact text from TradingView
- **Cause:** why it happens
- **Fix:** how to resolve

//@version=6
// ❌ Wrong
// ✅ Correct
```

Append this format to LESSONS_LEARNED.md after every error fix.
